body.name: HP S650 960GB 2.5 Inch SATA III PC SSD Internal Solid State Hard Drive - 6 Gb/s, 3D NAND, Up to 560 MB/s for Laptop and Desktop Updating - 345N0AA#ABA
features: Large capacity: 120GB/240GB/480GB/960GB/1.92TB five capacity options to meet the needs of office and entertainment to photo, videos, documents and other data storage.

Strong compatibility and easy upgrade: The classic 2.5" hard drive desigh allows the HP S650 to be compatible with mainstream desktop and laptop computers, makeing it easy to upgrade storage space on old computers and manage data.
Fast response: It is equipped with high quality components and high performance master control which dramatically improves system response with incredible boot, load document transfer time.

Office efficiency: Adopting 3D NAND flash memory components, supporting mechanisms such as LDPC ECC error correction and intelligent SLC cache, configured with SATA 3.0 high-speed interface, the maximum read and write speed can reach 560 MB/s, 500 MB/s.
After-sales service: 3-year limited warranty, only replacement without repair, free technical support.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars 5.0 out of 5 stars Value priced, meets or exceeds description, works as advertised and is a value.
reviews.reviewText: I purchase several things on Amazon and was giving pretty in-depth reviews. From this point on, here's the new agenda…. if it works as advertised, is well made, meets or exceeds the description, is a value, and arrives in a fair amount of time, it will get a "star rating" equal to what my expectations were/are. If it doesn't meet these criteria, then I will most definitely and descriptively tell the short comings of the products and you as a consumer will not have to go through the trouble of buying the product without some background knowledge. If the sell pulls that item and relists under another description, I will put the exact same review on the seller's feedback page. Sellers have done this a couple of times in the past, and I was true to my word then as well as now. DR

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good performance step up for an aging game machine
reviews.reviewText: I have a lot of games on my old gamer. Still runs great. But I was running out of room. I needed a one terabyte disk. I rushed my decision and bought a two terabyte hard disk. Then I thought better of it. I shopped for a solid state disk. After browsing this one seemed to be the best. I clicked submit and got it in a few days. I then went through the painful and laborious process of moving the entire contents of my system disk to the SS drive. After an hour or so I booted from the new disk. I could tell right away it was snappier. Cut the boot time in half. Now I’ll wind up filling this one up.Good drive. No issues. Solid performance. Highly recommend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars ~1TB of SSD Storage that works great
reviews.reviewText: I recently had to open up a several-year-old Dell XPS13 to replace the swollen battery pack. As long as I had it open I replaced the SSD too. I bought one of these because the price was so good and have not regretted it. Installed easily, as expected. Workes great, as expected. Lots of space, as expected. It was a nice upgrade.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 26, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars You're on your own for the install - but one it's installed it's AWESOME!!
reviews.reviewText: I'm pretty handy with computers and have worked tech support in the past. I thought this would be an easy install, but it wasn't. The only documentation that came with a small brochure with an 800 number that no one ever answered.In order to find the Acronis software that was supposed to come with it, I had to circle back to the product page on Amazon and read about it there. I was replacing an old HDD and ran the Acronis software to create a new bootable SSD. I ran it in the recommended automatic install and I ended up with 250 useable gigs and around 750 unallocated, meaning I couldn't do anything with it.On the Acronis website I was sent through a labyrinth of links that took me to create an account with a reg key, which isn't provided since this is an OEM with HP. No help there.I finally figured it out and got my 1T SSD working and it's absolutely amazing and super fast.5-stars for the SSD0-stars for the support because there is no support

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars drive works great, acronis included per description
reviews.reviewText: I used the included software/drive to replace a boot drive that gave me a "insert or replace disk" scare last week. Quick, easy and painless. After downloading from the link in the product description, the oem Acronis activates itself when it detects the drive, didnt need to enter any license keys for it. This drive has more space than the previous and seems to perform about the same, no complaints. Copied an 8GB file at 500+MB/s.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Quality SSD, easy install and upgrade.
reviews.reviewText: At first I bought a cheap no name drive. Figured they are all the same, right. Wrong! The cheap drive failed and lead to a weeks of frustration and hassle. Once I ended that debacle, I returned to Amazon to buy a real name brand. This HP is still a good value, and not as pricey as some others. If it fails within a couple years, Ill report back. So far it runs my machine fast and smooth. very pleased
